  "text": "Effect of ␣-synuclein mutations on ␣-synuclein localization ␣-Synuclein is highly enriched in presynaptic terminals [CITATION_1] , consistent with its role in promoting SNARE-complex assembly [CITATION_2] . Immunolocalization studies in cultured neurons from WT mice revealed a high degree of ␣-synuclein colocalization with the synaptic vesicle marker synapsin, measured using Pearson's coefficient (Fig. 3 A, B) . The ␣-synuclein colocalization was almost as high as that of the synaptic vesicle protein synaptobrevin-2. In cultured neurons from synaptobrevin-2 KO mice (Schoch et al., 2001 ), the synaptic localization of ␣-synuclein was significantly decreased (Fig. 3 A, B) . However, no change in synaptobrevin-2 localization was de- Figure 5 . Effects of ␣-synuclein mutations on the ␣-synuclein mediated catalysis of SNARE-complex assembly measured via the SDS-resistance of SNARE complexes. A, B, Cultured neurons from synuclein triple KO (TKO) mice were infected at 7DIV with lentivirus overexpressing WT and mutant ␣-synuclein. At 21 DIV, neurons were harvested and SNARE-complexes were measured as the high molecular mass bands immunoreactive for SNAP-25, which disappear upon boiling. ␣-Syn, ␣-synuclein; Synt-1, syntaxin-1; Syb2, synaptobrevin-2. B, Quantitation of SNARE-complex assembly upon overexpression of WT and mutant ␣-synucleins, normalized to control levels. Data are means Ϯ SEM (*p Ͻ 0.05, **p Ͻ 0.01, ***p Ͻ 0.001 by Student's t test; n ϭ 3 independent cultures).",
